<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,352,487]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">
Diagnosis:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. Fan &amp; T. Y. Zhao" authorityYear="2022" box="[284,530,352,378]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Gerronema" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="confusum">
<emphasis box="[284,530,352,378]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Gerronema confusum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="PBM" authorityYear="1250" box="[692,840,352,378]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Gerronema" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="atrialbum">
<emphasis box="[692,840,352,378]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">G. atrialbum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[903,1049,352,378]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Gerronema" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="wildpretii">
<emphasis box="[903,1049,352,378]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">G. wildpretii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the appearance of basidiomata, however it can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[582,728,388,414]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Gerronema" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="wildpretii">
<emphasis box="[582,728,388,414]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">G. wildpretii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having larger basidiospores (7.5–12.5 × 5–10 μm) and the absence of clamp connections in all tissues, while from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="PBM" authorityYear="1250" box="[745,888,424,450]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Gerronema" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="atrialbum">
<emphasis box="[745,888,424,450]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">G. atrialbum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having shorter stipe (
<quantity box="[1151,1233,424,451]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" unit="cm" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7 cm</quantity>
long) and abundant cheilocystidia. ITS-phylogeny supported 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. Fan &amp; T. Y. Zhao" authorityYear="2022" box="[600,741,460,486]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Gerronema" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="confusum">
<emphasis box="[600,741,460,486]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">G. confusum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a distinct species.
</paragraph>
